8:
Who would imagine... the place so
many utterly different individuals
gather could look so grand?
12:
I'll introduce you to the caretaker
here. She should be around...
16:
What should we do for Halloween,
Sir Alk? I was thinking you, Lady Nao,
and I could...
24:
It's been some time, Cel. You seem
to be quite well.
29:
You, too... I was so worried about you
that I kept thinking of running off to
the Farlands.
33:
Ah, is that so... I apologize for
worrying you, Cel.
36:
There were reports from numerous
locations of a "Blade rushing
through battlefields like a gale
force," but perhaps they were just
imagining things.
39:
Well met, Mayor of Starview Village.
This is truly an honor.
44:
Oh... N-no, I'm not the mayor or
anything...
51:
Sir Alk, perhaps instead of a
standard greeting...
66: S-sorry, but... I need a break...
70: Not bad, really... Not bad. But still...
75:
Is something wrong? You seem
disappointed.
79:
No, it's nothing. I was merely curious
what level of skill a man would have
to have to earn your interest.
82: But now, Cel, I'd like to spar with you!
90:
For what purpose do you think I
brought this blade? I have no
intention of losing.
95:
Sir Alk, please watch and learn how
to defeat Ciel.
99:
All right, my brother! Prepare
yourself!
110:
Ahem. My apologies, Sir Alk. I got a
bit carried away.
114:
N-not at all! I'm glad you two
enjoyed yourselves...
118:
While it's true that I wanted to visit
my sister... I actually wanted to
thank you.
121:
And not just for my sister or the
monster attack... I hear you and your
friends also helped out during the
attack on the peace treaty
ceremony.
125:
Oh, everyone tends to join in on their
own. It's not really because of me or
anything.
129:
Still, you have many ties to Palpebra,
Shibuya, and others... Surely, you are
also concerned about the Farlands?
132:
I feel the same. I want a solution that
improves both our situations... and
the power to discover that solution.
135:
Will you work with me on bettering
our relationship? I promise that I'll do
whatever I can to make it worth the
effort.
139:
I'm not looking to be used. That goes
for anyone here, I'm sure.
142:
But I'm definitely all for cooperating...
That's probably why Yuwel brought
you here.
145:
I'll put some more tea on. I'm sure
you've got a lot more questions.
150:
...I understand, now. That's what you
like about him, Cel.
154:
As I stated... Sir Alk and I do not have
such a relationship!
159:
While the tea service is appreciated,
perhaps you could teach me your
fighting style instead? You... were
holding back before, I believe.
164:
Well, I d-didn't mean to do it, really...
Just... trying to be diplomatic?
168:
I would know you as a swordsman,
Sir Alk, in the name of furthering our
relationship.
172: All right... Looking forward to it.
176:
Just like I thought, their personalities
don't fit together very well.
180:
I believe you may be incorrect there.
The two of them seem quite well
suited to one another, in my opinion!
187:
Hey... You're not scheming up some
kinda trouble, are ya?
191:
I assure you, I am merely
exchanging greetings. We just
happened to meet.
194:
Scheming would be better suited to
those who would associate with the
man known as the Traitor of Oinas.
198:
Tch. You don't need t' hang around if
ya can't take it. A whole lotta hard
truths are about to come out.
202:
Not a chance. I believe this is
necessary. I have no intention of
leaving now.
206:
Quit it with the formal talk, would
ya? The name's Vyron. I ain't some
lord worthy of talk like that.
209:
Anyway, what do you think of all this,
O Great Lord of Tris?
213:
I am struck with such wonder that I
must not let others from the
Farlands know about it.
216:
If people knew that this group was
behind the sudden increase in
Palpebra's might, it would cause
another terrible stir among them.
220:
You don't think anyone in Palpebra's
up to anything... do ya?
224:
Perhaps not... but SOME might be.
I'm more concerned with gossip
among the religious groups.
227:
"Palpebra is fighting against visitors
from the sky," for example.
231:
...I getcha. You really think the
Church of Farlana can spin it so
Palpebra is an affront to the Stars?
234:
Certainly seems like something
they'd try. When a man's drowning,
he'll grasp at anything he can, right?
238:
That is precisely why Azrail and I are
here, to put a stop to it.
241:
As of now, it is but a seed that might
lead to civil war. In order to uproot it,
perhaps joining the Traitor of Oinas
is not such a bad idea.
244:
...And those are my thoughts as a
lord. Now, let me speak as a
swordsman.
252: May I ask you for a sparring match?
256:
Whaddya talking about? You and
your sister are some kinda fighting
nuts!
264:
Heh-heh! You can't just go stealing
prey from your sister, though. Talk to
me after she's had a turn!
272:
I shall take my time and see it
through, then.
